# Post-Script Annotation Compliance

## Purpose

After the agent executes any project script, it must run a comment-annotation compliance check and auto-fix pass before reporting completion.

## Trigger

Apply this rule whenever the agent runs script commands such as:
- `pnpm run <script> -- ...`
- `node .cursor/scripts/...`
- `node .pantheon/.cursor/scripts/...`

## Standard File Format (MR !1600 aligned)

When checking or auto-fixing script annotations, use this exact structure:

1. **Top block**: `檔案用途區塊`
   - Must include: `@module`, `@purpose`
   - Optional: `@external` (only when an external reference is identifiable)
2. **Middle declaration blocks**: `宣告內容用途說明與單號關聯`
   - Must include: `@description`, `@purpose`
   - Optional: `@external` (same rule as above)
3. **Bottom block**: `llm 分析紀錄區`
   - Must include exactly one block per file
   - Must include: `@llm-review-submitted-at`, `@llm-review-model`, `@llm-review-note`

### Required Formatting Rules

- Use plain section titles (`檔案用途區塊`, `宣告內容用途說明與單號關聯`, `llm 分析紀錄區`).
- Do not use decorative title wrappers such as `=== ... ===`.
- If no external reference is confidently identifiable, do not emit `@external`.
- If `@external` is emitted, it must be a full hyperlink:
  - `@external https://example.com/path/to/reference`
- Keep only one `llm 分析紀錄區` block (dedupe old records).

### Canonical Example

```js
/**
 * 檔案用途區塊
 * @module external-sync
 * @purpose 更新外部系統資料同步行為
 * @external https://docs.example.com/specs/external-sync
 */

/**
 * 宣告內容用途說明與單號關聯
 * @description 建立外部 API 認證設定
 * @purpose 支援同步流程所需的請求簽章與授權
 * @external https://docs.example.com/api/auth
 */
function createApiConfig() {}

/**
 * llm 分析紀錄區
 * @llm-review-submitted-at 2026-06-14T00:00:00.000Z
 * @llm-review-model gpt-5.4-nano
 * @llm-review-note 註解格式對齊標準，未變更 runtime 邏輯。
 */
```

## Mandatory Steps

1. Detect whether script-related files were touched (especially `.cursor/scripts/**/*.mjs`).
2. Run external-link normalization first:
   - `pnpm run evolve -- fix-external-links --dirs=.cursor/scripts --format=text`
3. Run safe annotation auto-fix:
   - `pnpm run evolve -- annotation-audit --dirs=.cursor/scripts --fix=true --format=text`
4. Run one verification pass:
   - `pnpm run evolve -- annotation-audit --dirs=.cursor/scripts --format=text`

## Enforcement Rules

- `@external` must either:
  - be a full hyperlink (for any valid external reference), or
  - be removed when no reliable external reference can be determined.
- Auto-fix actions must remain comment-only and must not alter runtime logic.
- If verification still reports unresolved issues, the agent must report the file list and ask the user before any non-comment refactor.

## Reporting Requirement

When finishing script execution, include:
- number of scanned/updated files,
- how many invalid `@external` were normalized or removed,
- whether the final verification pass is clean.
